     ## Valcre Home Tab Model (Target Architecture)

     ### Valcre's 13 Sections (~114-133 fields)

     | Section | Fields | Purpose |
     |---------|--------|---------|
     | **1. Setup** | Property Type, Subtype, Modules | Drives entire report
     structure |
     | **2. Approach Toggles** | Income/Cost/Sales checkboxes | Controls which pages
     appear |
     | **3. Appraisal Info** | Company, Phone, Report Type | Letterhead,
     certification |
     | **4. Client Info** | Name, Company, Address, Contact | LOE, cover letter |
     | **5. Appraiser(s)** | Primary + Secondary + Credentials | Certification page |
     | **6. Valuation Scenarios** | As-Is, As-Stabilized, Prospective | Cover,
     reconciliation |
     | **7. Dates** | Effective, Report, Inspection, Letter | Throughout report |
     | **8. Subject Property** | Address, Legal, Units, NRA | Headers, property
     descriptions |
     | **9. Qualitative** | Quality, Appeal, Condition dropdowns | Site/building
     descriptions |
     | **10. Transaction History** | Previous sales, ownership | Ownership section |
     | **11. Conditions** | EA 1-4, HC 1-4, ELC 1-3 | Assumptions page |
     | **12. Occupancy** | Rates, Status | Income analysis |
     | **13. Words/Grammar** | Singular/plural auto-correct | Narrative text |

     ### Cascading Logic Pattern

     ```
     Property Type Selection
         ↓ (filters available subtypes)
     Property Subtype Selection
         ↓ (determines available modules)
     Module Toggles (Income/Cost/Sales)
         ↓ (controls page visibility)
     Report Pages Rendered
     ```

